Key Match Events: Fans threw objects onto the field causing a delay during the seventh inning
The Padres won the game tying the series 1-1
The game was marred by poor pitching and hitting from the Dodgers
Post-Match Reflections: Dodgers manager Dave Roberts expressed embarrassment over the fan behavior
Padres manager Mike Shildt mentioned the need to stay classy despite the hostile crowd
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was the second in the NLDS
Freddie Freeman left the game with a sprained ankle
The Padres had six home runs and a stolen home run in the game
